The paper proposes a new algorithmic framework for learning autoencoders of data distributions, which is a topic related to machine learning and deep learning. The paper also mentions that the proposed method outperforms existing methods on generating images, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is a likely sub-category. The use of fused Gromov-Wasserstein (FGW) distance and co-training of multiple autoencoders suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions real-world multi-view learning tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of computation and language (cs.CL).
